obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (30070)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00013_196063_1528788920819&sectionId=30070&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00013_196063_1528788920819
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be called the Preference Shares (Regulation of`
  line `Dividends) Act, 1960.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India:`
  line
  line `Provided that it shall not apply to the State of Jammu and Kashmir* except to the extend to which the`
  line `provision of this Act relate to the regulation of dividends on preference shares of banking and insurance`
  line `companies and financial corporations.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2) the provision of this Act shall, in their`
  line `application to the Union territory of Pondicherry, have effect subject to the modifications specified in the`
  line Schedule.]
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 1968, s. 3 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 24-5-1968).`
  line
  line `*. Vide notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu`
  line `and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (30071)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00013_196063_1528788920819&sectionId=30071&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00013_196063_1528788920819
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Companies Act," means the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(b) "company" means an Indian company as defined in ^2[clause (26) of section 2 of the Incometax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961) and includes a company referred to in sub-clause (ii) of clause (17)] of the`
  line `said section which has made arrangements for the declaration and payment of dividends within Indian`
  line `in accordance with the rules made under the said Act;`
  line
  line `(c) "preference share" means a share which ^3*** carries, as respects dividends, a preferential right`
  line `to be paid a fixed amount or an amount calculated at a fixed rate;`
  line
  line `(d) "previous year" has the same meaning as in the ^4[Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961)];`
  line
  line `(e) "stipulated dividend", in relation to a preference share, means the fixed amount or the amount`
  line `calculated at fixed rate which the holder of such share has a preferential right to be paid as dividend;`
  line
  line `(f) all other word and expressions used but not defined in this Act and defined in the Companies`
  line `Act shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 1965, s. 72, for "clause (7A) of section 2 of the Indian Income-tax Act, 1922 and includes a company`
  line `referred to in sub-clause (ii) of clause (5A)" (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `2. The words, figures and letters "having been issued and subscribed for before the 1st day of April, 1960" omitted by s. 72, ibid.`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 72, ibid., for "Indian Income-tax Act, 1922 (11 of 1922)" (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (30072)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Regulation of dividends on preference shares in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00013_196063_1528788920819&sectionId=30072&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00013_196063_1528788920819
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the stipulated`
  line `dividend in respect of a preference share of a company ^1[issued and subscribed for before the 1st April,`
  line 1960],--
  line
  line `(a) is specified to be free of income-tax and no deduction is made therefrom on account of the`
  line `income-tax payable by the company, or`
  line
  line `(b) was being paid before the 1st April, 1960, without any deduction therefrom on account of the`
  line `income-tax payable by the company, notwithstanding the absence of any specification that the`
  line `dividend would be free of income-tax,`
  line
  line `every such share shall, as respects dividends declared after the commencement of this Act, carry a`
  line `preferential right to be paid without any deduction aforesaid such amount as would exceed the stipulated`
  line `dividend by thirty per cent. thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the stipulated dividend in respect of preference share of a company issued and subscribed`
  line `for after the 31st March, 1959 ^2[and before the 1st April, 1960] is free of income-tax, and the company,`
  line `besides paying the stipulated dividend to the holder such share, pays to Government on his behalf any`
  line `sum on account of income-tax payable thereon, then, every such share shall, as respects dividends`
  line `declared after the commencement of this Act, carry a preferential right to be paid free of income-tax such`
  line `amount as together with the sum aforesaid would exceed the stipulated dividend by thirty per cent.`
  line thereof.
  line
  line `(3) Where the stipulated dividend in respect of a preference share of a company^2[issued and`
  line `subscribed for before the 1st April, 1960]--`
  line
  line `(a) is specified to be subject to income-tax and a deduction is made therefrom on account of the`
  line `income-tax payable by the company, or`
  line
  line `(b) was being paid before the 1st April, 1960, subject to a deduction therefrom on account of the`
  line `income-tax payable by the company, notwithstanding the absence of any specification that the`
  line `dividend would be subject to income-tax, then every such share shall, as respects dividends declared`
  line `after the commencement of this Act, carry a preferential right to be paid subject to the deduction`
  line `aforesaid such amount as would exceed the stipulated dividend by eleven percent.thereof.`
  line
  line `(4) Where a company has in relation to a preference share ^2[issued and subscribed for before the 1st`
  line `April, 1960] declared,--`
  line
  line `(a) after the 31st March, 1959, and before he 1st July, 1960, a dividend in respect of a previous`
  line `year relevant to its assessment year 1960-61 or a subsequent assessment year, or`
  line
  line `(b) after the 30th June, 1960, and before the commencement of this Act, a dividend in respect of`
  line `any previous year,`
  line
  line `it shall declare, in respect of the said previous year, an additional dividend of such amount as, together`
  line `with the dividend already declared, would exceed the stipulated dividend--`
  line
  line `(i)by thirty per cent.of the stipulated dividend in the cases referred to in sub-section (1), or`
  line
  line `(ii) by eleven per cent. of the stipulated dividend in the cases referred to in sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(5) For the purposes of sub-section (1), sub-section (3) and sub-section (4), any reference therein to`
  line `the stipulated dividend shall, in respect of a preference share issued and subscribed for on or before the`
  line `31st March, 1959, be construed as a reference to the stipulated dividend as on that day.`
  line
  line `(6) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that any reference in this section ^2[and section 4A]`
  line `to deduction made from a dividend "on account of income-tax payable by the company" does not include`
  line `any amount deducted by the company from the dividend under ^3[section 194 of the Income-tax Act,`
  line `1961(43 of 1961)].`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 72, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 10 of 1965, s. 72 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 72, ibid., for "sub-section (3D) of section 18 of the Indian Income-tax Act, 1922 (11 of 1922)" (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (30073)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Special provisions in relation to companies where a portion of their income is not chargeable to income-tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00013_196063_1528788920819&sectionId=30073&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00013_196063_1528788920819
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `^1[Where any preference share of a company has been issued and subscribed for before`
  line `the 1st April, 1960, and any portion of the profits and gains of the company] in respect of the relevant`
  line `period is exempt from income-tax under the ^2[Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961)], by reason of such portion being agricultural income, then, for the purpose of the increase in the dividend in relation to any`
  line `such preference share under the provisions of section 3, the increase of thirty per cent. or eleven per cent.`
  line `referred to therein shall be taken to be such proportion of the said thirty per cent. or eleven per cent. as the`
  line `case may be, as the total amount of the profits and gains of the company excluding the portion of the`
  line `profits and gains which is so exempt in respect of the relevant period bears to the total amount of the`
  line `profits and gains thereof in respect of that period.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purpose of this section, "relevant period", in relation to the profits and gains of`
  line `a company, shall mean--`
  line
  line `(a) the previous years relevant to such of the three assessment years as immediately precede the`
  line `assessment year ending on the 31st March, 1961, and in each of which the net result of the`
  line `computation of profits and gains of the company has not been loss or where there are only two such`
  line `years, such two years, or where there is only one such year, such one year; or`
  line
  line `(b) in any case where clause (a) is not applicable, the previous year relevant to the assessment`
  line `year ending on the 31st March, 1961 or a subsequent assessment year immediately following`
  line `thereafter in which the net result of the computation of profits and gains has not been a loss.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 72, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 72, ibid., for "Indian Income-tax Act, 1922 (11 of 1922)" (w.e.f 1-4-1965).`
obj_root_law_sections_4_a:
  sectionId (30074)
  sectionNo 4A
  orderNo 5
  title `Deduction of income-tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00013_196063_1528788920819&sectionId=30074&sectionno=4A&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00013_196063_1528788920819
obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[4A. Deduction of income-tax.-- Where the stipulated dividend in respect of a preference share of a`
  line company--
  line
  line `(a) is specified to be subject to income-tax and a deduction is made therefrom on account of the`
  line `income-tax payable by the company, or`
  line
  line `(b) is being paid subject to a deduction therefrom on account of the income-tax payable by the`
  line `company, notwithstanding the absence of any specification that the dividend would be subject to`
  line income-tax,
  line
  line `^2[such deduction made by the company from any dividend declared after the 28th day of February, 1966`
  line `shall in no case exceed twenty-seven and a half per cent. of the aggregate of--`
  line
  line `(i) the stipulated dividend, and`
  line
  line `(ii) an amount equal to eleven per cent. of the stipulated dividend as specified in sub-section (3)`
  line `of section 3.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 1965, s. 72 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 13 of 1966, s. 52, for certain words, figures, letters and brackets (w.e.f. 1-4-1966).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (30075)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 6
  title `Over-riding effect of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00013_196063_1528788920819&sectionId=30075&sectionno=5&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00013_196063_1528788920819
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1)The provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything to the contrary contained in any law for the time being in force or in the memorandum or articles`
  line `of a company or in any agreement between the company and its shareholders or in any resolution passed`
  line `by the company in a general meeting or by its Board of directors.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, a company may, in the manner provided in`
  line `section 106 of the Companies Act, increase the amount of dividend in respect of a preference shall`
  line `beyond the limit specified in section 3 or section 4 of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (30076)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Act not to apply to participating preference dividends.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 1965, s. 72, for "this Act" (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00013_196063_1528788920819&sectionId=30076&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00013_196063_1528788920819
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in ^1[section 3 or`
  line `section 4] shall apply to such part of any dividend on preference shares as is referred to in clause (i) of the`
  line `Explanation to sub-section (1) of section 85 of the Companies Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (30077)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00013_196063_1528788920819&sectionId=30077&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00013_196063_1528788920819
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made under this section shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made before each`
  line `House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session in which it is so laid or the`
  line `session immediately following, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses`
  line `agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or`
  line `be of no effect, as the case may be, so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without`
  line `prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
